column45: Gaited breed of horse that originated in America and are the state horse of Alabama. They are known for their singlefoot gait.
Naturally gaited horse breed characterized by spotted color patterns such as tobiano and overo.
The Persian sheep is a fat-tailed breed of domestic sheep from Somalia, Africa, bred primarily for meat.

An American breed of horse founded in Nebraska in the early to mid 20th century. The founder was an all white ("albino") horse, which all is the predominant phenotypic trait in all members of the breed today. The breed was later used as in circuses, movies, and as pleasure horses.
An American breed of draft horse known for their leopard coat color.
An American breed of draft horse developed in the mid to late 20th century. Like American Albinos, they are known for their all-white coat color.
The Blazer Horse is a small breed of riding horse developed in Wyoming in the mid 20th century.
The Carolina Marsh Tacky is a gaited breed of horse descended from Colonial Spanish horses and is only found in South Carolina.
A feral breed of ponies found on the island of Assateague, Virginia/Maryland.
An American breed of riding horse founded in Montana, known for their hardiness and running-walk gait

A type of Spanish of riding horse that was brought to the Americas during colonization. These horses were foundational to many North and South American breeds of horses and the modern Spanish breeds. Recent efforts are reviving the breed using Jennet type horses found in modern breeds.
An American breed of sport horse horse developed in California in the late 20th century and early 21st century. They are known for their leopard coat color and versatility.
An American breed of gaited horse known for their spotted coat and smooth gaits

An American breed of harness horse developed developed with Standardbreds, Hackney Horses, Welsh Ponies, and Shetland Ponies. They can be found at Trottingbred races in the Midwest of the United States.
